div.p:
Power of Commissioners.
4. That they may decree Lands given to Charitable Uses, to sundry persons and their Heirs, to the said Vses, and enable them to demise the said Lands for the best profit of the said Charitable Use;
To order the settlement of the Land charged. and that when such a number of them shall dye, the survivors shall make a Conveyance to settle the same Lands in themselves that survive, and others to make up, and continue the number by them appointed. Seé for this, Chap. 6. Case 2, 5.
